# New Composition вЂ” Mandatory Registration Checklist

Every time a new composition file is created in `src/compositions/`, you MUST
register it in **both** of the following files before the task is considered done.
Never skip either step. Never ask the user to do it manually.

---

## Step 1 вЂ” `src/Root.tsx`

Add a `<Composition>` block inside `RemotionRoot`. Match the format of existing entries:

```tsx
// LangEaseAd вЂ” 9:16, 18s вЂ” brief description
<Composition
  id="langease-v1"
  component={LangEaseAd}
  durationInFrames={540}
  fps={30}
  width={1080}
  height={1920}
  defaultProps={{}}
/>
```

- Import the component at the top of `Root.tsx`
- `id` must be kebab-case and end with a version suffix (e.g. `-v1`)
- `width`/`height` must match the composition's intended format (9:16 = 1080Г—1920, 1:1 = 1080Г—1080, 16:9 = 1920Г—1080)

---

## Step 2 вЂ” `studio/src/registry.ts`

Add an entry to the `REGISTRY` array. This is what makes the composition visible in the custom Studio UI:

```ts
// в”Ђв”Ђ LangEaseAd в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
{
  id:               "langease-v1",           // must match Root.tsx id
  label:            "LangEase вЂ” Translate. Dub. Distribute.",
  component:        LangEaseAd,
  durationInFrames: 540,
  fps:              30,
  width:            1080,
  height:           1920,
  format:           "9:16",
  defaultProps:     {},
  sequences: [
    { id: "s1", label: "Hook",     from: 0,   durationInFrames: 90,  color: CLR.hook     },
    { id: "s2", label: "Platform", from: 90,  durationInFrames: 135, color: CLR.product  },
    { id: "s3", label: "Features", from: 225, durationInFrames: 135, color: CLR.features },
    { id: "s4", label: "Tagline",  from: 360, durationInFrames: 90,  color: CLR.metrics  },
    { id: "s5", label: "CTA",      from: 450, durationInFrames: 90,  color: CLR.cta      },
  ],
},
```

- Import the component at the top of `registry.ts` using the `@comps/` alias (e.g. `import { LangEaseAd } from "@comps/LangEaseAd"`)
- `sequences` should reflect the actual scene breakdown in the composition
- Use the `CLR` colour constants: `CLR.hook`, `CLR.product`, `CLR.features`, `CLR.metrics`, `CLR.cta`, `CLR.generic`
- `label` should be human-readable with a short tagline

---

## Sequence colours reference

```ts
const CLR = {
  hook:     "#0ea5e9",  // sky     вЂ” S1
  product:  "#8b5cf6",  // violet  вЂ” S2
  features: "#10b981",  // emerald вЂ” S3
  metrics:  "#f59e0b",  // amber   вЂ” S4
  cta:      "#ef4444",  // red     вЂ” S5
  generic:  "#6366f1",  // indigo  вЂ” extra scenes
};
```

---

## Format reference

| Format | width | height | format string |
|--------|-------|--------|---------------|
| 9:16   | 1080  | 1920   | `"9:16"`      |
| 1:1    | 1080  | 1080   | `"1:1"`       |
| 16:9   | 1920  | 1080   | `"16:9"`      |

---

## Why both files are required

- **`src/Root.tsx`** вЂ” Remotion's renderer reads this. Without it, `npm run render` won't find the composition.
- **`studio/src/registry.ts`** вЂ” The custom Studio UI reads this. Without it, the composition won't appear in the left panel or timeline. This is why the user has to "keep asking" вЂ” only one of the two was being updated.

Both must be updated in the **same session** that creates the composition file.

---

## Duration Sync Checklist

When changing the total duration of a composition (adding/removing scenes, extending `SceneFade dur`), update **all three locations**:

| Location | Field to update |
|----------|----------------|
| `src/compositions/*.tsx` | `SceneFade dur` prop on the affected scene |
| `src/Root.tsx` | `durationInFrames` on the `<Composition>` |
| `studio/src/registry.ts` | `durationInFrames` on the registry entry AND the matching sequence's `durationInFrames` |

**All three must match.** If they don't:
- Remotion will render the wrong number of frames (Root.tsx mismatch)
- Studio timeline will show wrong scene boundaries (registry mismatch)
- Scenes will overlap or cut short (SceneFade mismatch)

### Quick check after any duration change:
```
grep -n "durationInFrames" src/Root.tsx studio/src/registry.ts | grep "composition-id"
```

Verify the numbers match. This is the #1 source of "why does my scene cut off?" bugs.

---

## Category & Subcategory

Every registry entry should include `category` and `subcategories` for scoped knowledge lookup:

```ts
category: "saas",
subcategories: ["text-animation", "ui-elements", "transitions"],
```

Available categories are defined in `src/data/categories/*.json`. If a composition doesn't fit an existing category, create a new JSON file.
